            <title>[HTTPCLIENT-1100] Missing Content-Length header makes cached entry invalid</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/HTTPCLIENT-1100</link>
                <project id="12310360" key="HTTPCLIENT">HttpComponents HttpClient</project>
                        <description>A cached entry whose original response didn&amp;#39;t carry a Content-Length header, should not be rejected for considered invalid because the length of its cached content is different from the non-existing Content-Length header value. The attached patch only verifies the lengths if the header was originally present.</description>
