                    <comment id="13046555" author="jonm" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2011 15:09:15 +0100"  >Hi Bart,&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Your patch looks great, although we need you to grant license to the ASF to include your patch. Can you either edit your attachment to grant ASF permission, or re-upload it with the proper permissions?&lt;br/&gt;
&lt;br/&gt;
Thanks,&lt;br/&gt;
Jon&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
                    <comment id="13046559" author="jonm" created="Thu, 9 Jun 2011 15:12:48 +0100"  >By the way, I suppose this is presumed by my earlier response, but I agree this is a bug. The cache entry should only be considered invalid if there is a Content-Length header present and it does not match the length of the cached response body. If a Content-Length header is not present, then the entry should be presumed valid (at least per the sense of this test).&lt;br/&gt;
</comment>
